# Specify download directory so the  version -c  or  version -r  commands can retrive dCore updates.
# The full dCore boot pathway should be specified below (contains the dCore-*.gz and vmlinuz-* files).
# The version command will automatically back up the old dCore-*.gz and *.md5.txt files before
# downloading the update. Reboot system to complete the update.
#
# If this file is modified, add an /opt/.filetool.lst entry to save changes:
#      etc/sysconfig/boot_path
#
# ONLY ONE UNCOMMENTED LINE ALLOWED, NO SPACES OR EMPTY LINES
#
# ENTRY MUST START WITH A SLASH
# 
# ENTRY MUST CONTAIN /mnt/* IF DESTINATION IS NOT MOUNTED AFTER BOOT
#
# Note dCore uses the symlink 'tcedir' to point to the /tce directory. The dCore installer by default uses
# /etc/sysconfig/tcedir/boot, on the actual system this may be something like /mnt/sdb4/tce/boot.
#
# Example entries:
#/etc/sysconfig/tcedir/boot
#/mnt/sdb4/tce/boot
#
/etc/sysconfig/tcedir/boot